article_id:976,category_name:Events,title_name:A Raid Event Revival, New Year's Tidings: Fortune from Afar, Is Now Live!,image_path:https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/31790c9453ccbeb3ffd79cf78bcfcad5.png,message:<div>Up to four players with four adventurers each (up to 16 adventurers in total!) can battle together in the New Year&#39;s Tidings: Fortune from Afar raid event revival, which began <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1577340000"></span>. Take on event-specific quests to defeat the light-attuned raid boss and earn rewards!</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/31790c9453ccbeb3ffd79cf78bcfcad5.png"></div><div>The new year is almost upon the Halidom! A group of people bringing blessings for the new year in samurai attire arrive from Hinomoto, a land to the east. But when a naginata-wielding young woman who was following that group shows up, the Halidom is thrown into an uproar! Will they all be able to safely ring in the new year?<br><br>An adventurer, Botan, will join you during this event. Increase your friendship with her to add her to your roster permanently. You can also collect blazons and emblems to get the dragon Shishimai and the Luck of the Draw wyrmprint.<br><br>Find the New Year&#39;s Tidings: Fortune from Afar raid event revival details below.<br><br>■Additions<br><br>1. Refreshed rewards<br>The kagami mochi in the boss battle may now drop succulent dragonfruit, consecrated water, and other upgrade items.<br>The raid boss&#39;s gift basket may now drop items that confer augments.<br>The raid battle will also sometimes drop shadow-attuned weapons.<br>Use the rewards you get to upgrade your adventurers!<br><br>2. Blazon summoning<br>You will now be able to get wyrmite via blazon summoning.<br><br>■Event Duration<br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1577340000"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1577771999"></span><br>・If the event ends while you are in a quest, the quest will continue until the results have been determined. You will be able to earn rewards according to the results of the quest.<br><br>■Reward Availability Period<br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1577340000"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1578376799"></span><br>・You will be able to perform blazon summons and obtain emblem rewards during this period.<br><br>■Temporary Adventurers<br>When you complete quests, you will increase the friendship with any temporary adventurers in your team. If you maximize your friendship with a temporary adventurer, they will permanently remain in your collection, allowing you to include them in your team after the event ends. Their level, stats, equipment, and position in your team and collection will be maintained.<br><br>Note: Even if an event adventurer isn&#39;t permanently added to your collection, any items used to upgrade their level, unlock their mana circles, and promote them will not be returned.<br><br>■If Botan Previously Joined as a Temporary Adventurer<br>You can include Botan in your team again when this event starts, and she will maintain the same level and stats as when this event was held previously.<br><br>■Raid Battles<br>Raid battles are co-op battles where up to four teams (16 adventurers) can cooperate against a raid boss together! There are three difficulty levels available: Beginner, Expert, and Nightmare.<br>To participate in a raid battle, you must either create a room as the host or join a room as a guest.<br><br>・As a Host:<br>Creating a room requires otherworld fragments and getherwings.<br>You can obtain otherworld fragments from boss battles.<br><br>・As a Guest:<br>Joining a room requires otherworld fragments and getherwings.<br>You must have unlocked the respective difficulty to participate in a raid battle.<br><br>■Extra Raid Battles<br>You must clear the raid battle on Expert.<br><br>・As a Host:<br>Creating a room requires an otherworld gem.<br>You can obtain otherworld gems from the Expert and Nightmare difficulty raid battles.<br><br>・As a Guest:<br>Joining a room requires an otherworld gem.<br>You must have cleared the Expert difficulty to participate in a raid battle.<br><br>■Regarding Omega Difficulty<br>There will be no Omega difficulty quests this time.<br><br>■Blazon Summons<br>Complete boss battles and raid battles to obtain peregrine blazons. Blazons collected can be used for blazon summoning to get event-specific 5★ dragons, 4★ wyrmprints, and other rewards.<br>After obtaining the dragon Shishimai through summoning, you can reset the contents available.<br>From the 5th reset onward, you must accept all rewards before you can reset the contents available.<br><br>■Emblems<br>You can obtain rewards, such as event-specific wyrmprints, based on the total number of emblems you gather during the event.<br><br>■Event Endeavors<br>Two types of event endeavors will be available during the event: Daily and Limited.<br><br>■Epilogue<br>The epilogue for the New Year&#39;s Tidings: Fortune from Afar revival event will unlock at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1577772000"></span>.<br>Note: To view the epilogue, you must complete chapter 8 of the event story.<br><br>■Epilogue Availability<br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1577772000"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1578376799"></span><br><br>Notes:<br>1. During raid battles, you will only recover 1/4 of the amount of HP from certain skills and abilities.<br>2. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign to participate in event quests.<br>3. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign in order to play co-op.<br>4. If you do not maximize your friendship with temporary adventurers during the event, they will not join you after the event ends, regardless of their level or stats.<br>5. If a temporary adventurer permanently joins your roster, you will be able to read their Adventurer Story.<br>6. You will not be able to use blazons, emblems, otherworld gems, or otherworld fragments obtained in this event in future events.<br>7. For details concerning this raid event, check the Help section on the raid event&#39;s top page in the game.<br><br>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1577340000,update_time1577265900